Trivia

Original Jhin
  •  
       "I live for the applause, you will die for it." references Applause by Lady Gaga.
  •  
       "It is by my will alone I set my mind in motion." references the Dune movie.
  •  
       " You have too many lines." references the River King having the most quotes in the game.
    • Ironically, Jhin has 241 lines (not counting vocal grunts) while Tahm Kench has about 224.
  •  
       "I love to perform, but I hate crowds." references spell shields being able to block crowd control effects.
  •  
       " Rapid fire? Where's the drama in that?" references his need for flair when using Whisper.
  •  
       "Happiness… is a warm gun." references the eponymous song by The Beatles.
    • This quote also shares similarity to 
      alttext=Pulsefire skin
         "Happiness is a thermally active temporal blaster."
  • In the Italian localization his selection quote "Cadranno come, d'Autunno, dagli alberi, le foglie.", They'll fall, like Autumn's leaves from trees) references the poem Soldati ('Soldiers') written by Italian Writer and Poet Giuseppe Ungaretti.
  •  
       "Sing for me!" references The Phantom of the Opera's song by Andrew Lloyd Webber.
  •  
       "They're puppets. I pull their strings, and then they dance." resembles  
       "Pull the strings. Watch them dance."
  •  
       "Behind every mask... is another mask." might be referencing Marty Rubin ("Behind every mask there is a face, and behind that a story."), Kakashi Hatake from Naruto ("Behind this mask... is another mask!") or even Luigi Pirandello.
  •  
       "This performance needs more… zazz." references Metalocalypse.
High Noon Jhin
  • When killing certain champions with Curtain Call, he speaks lines referencing various Western movies.
    •  
         "Kill Noxians and get paid for it? What's not to like?" and  
         "I like the way you die, boy." play on a quote from Django Unchained.
    •  
         "People scare better when they're dying." references Once Upon a Time in the West.
    •  
         "It's better to be above ground doing this than below ground doing nothing." quotes Django.
    •  
         "It's fun to kill a man, to take all that he had, and could ever have." references the movie that shares names with Yasuo's title.
    •  
         " You shoot to kill, you better hit the heart." quotes A Fistful of Dollars.
